ble on demand. A timely discussion of a topic whose worldwide impact continues to grow, this is essential reading for anyone concerned about the state of higher education - both for today's students and in the decades to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aPolitics and Government. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aEDUCATION / Administration / General.2bisacsh  aWetenschap, Universiteit, Onderwijs.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066284940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048535163zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048535163zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048535163/original  a978-3-11-066284-9 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA